               <children>
                  <TextArea maxHeight="1.7976931348623157E308" maxWidth="1.7976931348623157E308" text="This application was done as a school project to support physicist in research &#10;at the Commenius University in Slovakia. &#10;&#10;Application is free-to-use, open-source, and works with machine HP4191a. &#10;&#10;Project was built with Java 11 (maven) and Scenebuilder (javaFX). &#10;Dependency -  https://github.com/TIS2020-FMFI/hpctrl&#10;&#10;Credits belong to: &#10;Jakub Zak, Mariia Pikuleva, Richard Nagy, Jan Pastorek, Pavel Petrovic(supervisor)&#10;&#10;Machine tries to automatically connect GPIB, which can fail if hpctrl.exe&#10;is not on the correct adress/path within project. If this happens, you should check if the path&#10;is correct and if it is, try to connect manually by clicking on the GPIB connection button &#10;or try to reset the app. &#10;&#10;Measurement&#10;- runs by pressing run button, which also triggers graph visualization&#10;  * before pressing run you can set measurement input &#10;    parameters on the left and next to Save As button (Frequency/Voltage)&#10;  * if autosweep is ON, the measurement will run automatically, &#10;    if it is OFF, the measurement will continue by one step if you click on the next button&#10;&#10;- can be loaded into graph by pressing Load Button and finding measurement file&#10;- measurement is saved using Save As / Export button / autosave button (to file destination&#10;that you choose (next to this button). &#10;  When using Export button, you can include comments from comment area on the left.&#10;&#10;  When closes the application, the parameters of the last completed or loaded measurement &#10; are automatically saved. &#10;  &#10;Graph functionality&#10;- press ALT and drag mouse to pan a chart&#10;- press ALT and wheel up/down mouse to zoom a chart&#10;- select with mouse some part of chart and it will zoom&#10;- zoom back with draging to up-left corner&#10;- save plot by right-clicking and select export as&#10;- you can click on the point to see its value better with crosshair&#10;&#10;Calibration&#10;- user can calibrate using this app by pressing on the calibration button and running calibration&#10;  on short, open, load&#10;&#10;Directory for this project and contacts can be found here&#10;https://github.com/TIS2020-FMFI/hp&#10;&#10;HP 4191a Manual&#10;https://doc.xdevs.com/doc/HP_Agilent_Keysight/HP%204191A%20Operation%20&amp;%20Service.pdf&#10;&#10;" VBox.vgrow="ALWAYS" />
               </children>
            </VBox>
